data.chText: （用手指或其他东西）捅，戳，杵
data.enText: to quickly push your fingers or another object into sb/sth

data.chText: 她用胳膊肘顶他的肋部。
data.enText: She poked him in the ribs with her elbow.

data.chText: 她用胳膊肘顶他的肋部。
data.enText: She poked her elbow into his ribs.

data.chText: 我讨厌让医生在我身上戳戳点点的。
data.enText: I'm sick of being poked and prodded by doctors.

data.chText: 她起来拨了拨火。
data.enText: She got up and poked the fire (= to make it burn more strongly) .

data.chText: 推；捅；戳；探
data.enText: to push sth somewhere or move it in a particular direction with a small quick movement

data.chText: 他从转角处探出头来，查看有没有人过来。
data.enText: He poked his head around the corner to check that nobody was coming.

data.chText: 有人从门底下塞进了一张纸条。
data.enText: Someone had poked a message under the door.

data.chText: 别让那根棍子戳着她的眼！
data.enText: Don't poke her eye out with that stick!

data.chText: 露出；伸出；探出
data.enText: if an object is poking out of, through, etc. sth, you can see a part of it that is no longer covered by sth else

data.chText: 电缆头从墙里露出来了。
data.enText: The end of the cable was left poking out of the wall.

data.chText: 一簇簇的草破雪而出。
data.enText: Clumps of grass poked up through the snow.

data.chText: 捅窟窿；扎洞
data.enText: to make a hole in sth by pushing your finger or another object into it

data.chText: 孩子们用棍子在冰上戳洞。
data.enText: The kids poked holes in the ice with sticks.

data.enText: to say unkind things about sb/sth in order to make other people laugh at them

data.chText: 她的小说嘲弄上流社会。
data.enText: Her novels poke fun at the upper class.

data.chText: 搜查；翻找
data.enText: to look for sth, especially sth that is hidden among other things that you have to move

data.chText: 警察花了一天时间搜查他的办公室，但是没有发现什么情况。
data.enText: The police spent the day poking around in his office but found nothing.

data.chText: 我们让记者追着问了许多问题。
data.enText: We've had journalists poking around and asking a lot of questions.

example: I gave him a clout on his nose

tr: a sharp hand gesture (resembling a blow)
example: he warned me with a jab with his finger
he made a thrusting motion with his fist

tr: a bag made of paper or plastic for holding customer's purchases
someone who takes more time than necessary
tall coarse perennial American herb having small white flowers followed by blackish-red berries on long drooping racemes

example: he jabbed his finger into her ribs

tr: hit hard with the hand, fist, or some heavy instrument
example: the salesman pounded the door knocker
poke the embers in the fireplace

tr: search or inquire in a meddlesome way
example: This guy is always nosing around the office

value.def: If you poke someone or something, you quickly push them with your finger or with a sharp object.

example.ex: Lindy poked him in the ribs.
John smiled at them and gave Richard a playful poke.
example.tran: 约翰冲着他们笑了笑，开玩笑地捅了理查德一下。

value.def: If you poke one thing into another, you push the first thing into the second thing.

example.ex: He poked his finger into the hole.

value.def: If something pokes out of or through another thing, you can see part of it appearing from behind or underneath the other thing.

example.ex: He saw the dog's twitching nose poke out of the basket...
example.tran: 他看到那只狗一抽一抽的鼻子从篮子里冒出来。

example.ex: His fingers poked through the worn tips of his gloves.
example.tran: 他的手指从手套的破指尖处露了出来。

value.def: If you poke your head through an opening or if it pokes through an opening, you push it through, often so that you can see something more easily.

example.ex: Julie tapped on my door and poked her head in...
example.tran: 朱莉轻轻地敲了敲我的门，探进头来。

example.ex: We hadn't been able to poke our heads out and see what was going on...
example.tran: 我们无法伸出头去，看看发生了什么。

example.ex: Raymond's head poked through the doorway.
example.tran: 雷蒙德的头从门口探了出来。

xrse.def: to poke your nose into something
